itemDescription: Welsh jurist, politician and Regius Professor of Civil Law at the University of Oxford (1529–1595)

wikipedia_page.main: William Aubrey (c. 1529 – 25 June 1595) was Regius Professor of Civil Law at the University of Oxford from 1553 to 1559, and was one of the founding Fellows of Jesus College, Oxford. He was also a Member of Parliament for various Welsh and English constituencies between 1554 and 1592.
